4 approved restraint or securement systems where required by federal law."
5 SECTION 1.(e) G.S. 115C-150.12C is amended by adding a new subdivision to
6 read:
7 "(39) School transportation. – If the board of trustees purchases, leases, or rents any
8 school bus or activity bus for the purpose of providing transportation for
9 students, the board of trustees shall purchase, lease, or rent vehicles equipped
10 with type-two seat belt assemblies that are compliant with all applicable
11 regulations adopted under 49 U.S.C. § 30111 at all designated seating
12 positions, except the board of trustees may adopt reasonable policies
13 modifying this requirement with respect to integrated child safety restraint
14 systems, the transportation of students with disabilities, and the use of other
15 federally approved restraint or securement systems where required by federal
16 law."
17 SECTION 1.(f) Article 39 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended by
18 adding a new section to read:
19 "§ 115C-548.2. Transportation.
20 If a private church school or a school of religious charter purchases, leases, or rents any school
21 bus, as defined in federal motor vehicle safety standards, the private church school or school of
22 religious charter shall purchase, lease, or rent buses equipped with type-two seat belt assemblies
23 that are compliant with all applicable regulations adopted under 49 U.S.C. § 30111 at all
24 designated seating positions, except the private church school or school of religious charter may
25 adopt reasonable policies modifying this requirement with respect to integrated child safety
26 restraint systems, the transportation of students with disabilities, and the use of other federally
27 approved restraint or securement systems where required by federal law."
28 SECTION 1.(g) Article 39 of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes is amended by
29 adding a new section to read:
30 "§ 115C-566.2. Transportation.
31 If any qualified nonpublic school purchases, leases, or rents any school bus, as defined in
32 federal motor vehicle safety standards, the qualified nonpublic school shall purchase, lease, or
33 rent buses equipped with type-two seat belt assemblies that are compliant with all applicable
34 regulations adopted under 49 U.S.C. § 30111 at all designated seating positions, except the
35 qualified nonpublic school may adopt reasonable policies modifying this requirement with
36 respect to integrated child safety restraint systems, the transportation of students with disabilities,
37 and the use of other federally approved restraint or securement systems where required by federal
38 law."
39 SECTION 1.(h) G.S. 116-239.8(b) is amended by adding a new subdivision to read:
40 "(9a) If a laboratory school purchases, leases, or rents any school bus or activity bus
41 for the purpose of providing transportation for students, the laboratory school
42 shall purchase, lease, or rent vehicles equipped with type-two seat belt
43 assemblies that are compliant with all applicable regulations adopted under 49
44 U.S.C. § 30111 at all designated seating positions, except the laboratory
45 school may adopt reasonable policies modifying this requirement with respect
46 to integrated child safety restraint systems, the transportation of students with
47 disabilities, and the use of other federally approved restraint or securement
48 systems where required by federal law."
49 SECTION 2. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
50 Public Instruction the sum of ten thousand dollars ($10,000) for the 2026-2027 fiscal year for the
House Bill 1204-First Edition Page 3

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 purpose of developing policies that public school units may use to implement the requirements
2 of this act.
3 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law. G.S. 115C-240(c)(2)d., as
4 enacted by this act, applies to all contracts to purchase or lease school buses and activity buses
5 executed after June 30, 2030. This act shall not be construed to require any educational entity to
6 equip buses with seat belts at all designated seating positions if the buses are purchased or leased
7 before June 30, 2030.
